{
    "_comment": "gobj-ui declarative-shell demo. One primary menu (menu.primary) rendered as a VERTICAL rail on desktop (left) and an ICON-BAR on mobile (bottom) — that single pair already shows the per-zone responsive model. Each primary item is a chapter that demonstrates one SECONDARY layout in the content column: TABS (top-sub), SIDE SUBMENU (right), CARDS section-index + mobile BACKBAR, and a right-zone VERTICAL submenu. The toolbar burger opens a DRAWER (off-canvas vertical). The Accordion chapter has a direct target whose view embeds a live accordion nav (accordion is a primary-zone layout: its section bodies are the routable 2nd-level items, so it can't be a 3rd-level submenu). Every leaf mounts C_TEST_VIEW, which names on screen exactly which layout(s) are visible and where.",
    "shell": {
        "breakpoints": "bulma",
        "zones": {
            "top": {
                "host": "toolbar",
                "show_on": "*"
            },
            "left": {
                "host": "menu.primary",
                "show_on": ">=desktop"
            },
            "bottom": {
                "host": "menu.primary",
                "show_on": "<desktop"
            },
            "top-sub": {
                "host": "menu.secondary",
                "show_on": "*"
            },
            "right": {
                "host": "menu.secondary",
                "show_on": ">=desktop"
            },
            "center": {
                "host": "stage.main"
            }
        },
        "stages": {
            "main": {
                "zone": "center",
                "default_route": "/tabs"
            }
        },
        "routes": {
            "_sitemap_comment": "Action route (ROUTING.md 7.1): fires EV_OPEN_SITEMAP instead of mounting a view. redirect:'back' because the site map is a floating C_YUI_WINDOW on the overlay stack (no opener-owned URL hook, so 'stay' would leave the URL stale on close).",
            "/sitemap": {
                "kind": "action",
                "event": "EV_OPEN_SITEMAP",
                "redirect": "back"
            },
            "_prefs_comment": "The OTHER action-route flavour, and the reason it is here: redirect:'stay' keeps the URL on /prefs so the modal is deep-linkable, which means current_route stays on the resting view while the URL sits off it. That divergence is what the overlay/history bookkeeping has to survive (Back must still close the modal), and 'back' does not exercise it. Per ROUTING.md 7.1 'stay' is only correct when the opener owns the URL on close: ac_open_prefs' on_close does the history.back(), wattyzer's open_route_modal idiom.",
            "/prefs": {
                "kind": "action",
                "event": "EV_OPEN_PREFS",
                "redirect": "stay"
            }
        }
    },
